I"$<p>Timeshift is a simple application for newer to backup and restore Linux system.</p>

<h2 id="install-in-elementary-or-ubuntu">Install in elementary or Ubuntu</h2>

<ul>
  <li>sudo apt-add-repository ppa:teejee2008/ppa</li>
  <li>sudo apt-get update</li>
  <li>sudo apt-get install timeshift</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="backup">Backup</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>I selected RSYNC as snapshot type and chose to include /user and /root directories.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>You can also use other filters to select what you want to backup.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 id="restore">Restore</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Available snapshots will be shown in window.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Timeshift will create auto-snapshots every 5 days by default, if you want to, you can also create backups manually.</p>
  </li>
</ul>
:ET